  "original_title": "\u2018\u2018\u0dc0\u0dad\u0dca\u0db8\u0db1\u0dca \u0d86\u0dab\u0dca\u0da9\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0da7 \u0da2\u0db1\u0dad\u0dcf \u0dc4\u0dac\u0da7 \u0db8\u0dd4\u0dc4\u0dd4\u0dab \u0daf\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0db6\u0dd1\u2018\u2018",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "\"The current government cannot face the voice of the people\"",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The National Movement for a Just Society says in a statement that by arresting Mrs. Hirunika Premachandra along with a group of women, Rehan Jayawickrama and a group of other political activists in front of the President's residence in Colombo Fort, the current government has shown to the world the level of fear it is expressing without being able to face the voice of the people.",
        "Also, the statement issued by the President of the National Movement for a Just Society Mr. Karu Jayasuriya states that the level of hatred that the government is showing towards those who stand for the real issues of the people is also well displayed and Sri Lanka's dislike for democratic rights and freedom is also displayed. .",
        "The announcement has further emphasized that the National Movement for a Fair Society strongly condemns the incident and the government must understand that the people are not silent in the face of the enormous pressure they are facing."
      ],
